STEP 1
Input files:
- actual_truth_2026-04-24/Aveli_System_Decisions.md
Action:
- IF actual_truth_2026-04-24/Aveli_System_Decisions.md does not exist, STOP with condition: "Aveli_System_Decisions.md missing".
- IF file exists, extract the following explicit decisions:
  - API definitions = audit-driven catalog truth (API_CATALOG.json/markdown + usage diff)
  - Media control plane = control-plane required
  - Auth flow = security baseline only
Expected output:
- Decision alignment record with three fields: API source, Media scope, Auth constraint.
PASS condition:
- All three fields are present and map exactly to the approved options.
STOP if:
- Any field is absent or maps to a non-approved option.

RULE 1: API truth source (no change to logic)
IF a route is processed in any comparison step, THEN source-of-truth for API definitions is:
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_CATALOG.json
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_CATALOG.md
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_USAGE_DIFF.md
AND no route decisions may use docs/api_v2_reference.md as canonical.

RULE 2: Media control-plane protection
IF a route path belongs to media control-plane set in docs/media_control_plane_mcp.md, THEN
- action = DO NOT modify media_control_plane routes or docs.
- action = DO NOT remove route from media control-plane docs.
- action = DO NOT add changes to media control-plane route definitions.

RULE 3: Auth boundary protection
IF route file/path is part of auth system, THEN
- action = DO NOT redesign structure.
- action = route handling may only be aligned to security baseline from:
  - docs/SECURITY.md
  - docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/SECURITY_REVIEW.md
AND DO NOT alter auth boundary architecture in this phase.

RULE 4
Input files:
- backend/app/main.py
- backend/app/routes/*.py
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_CATALOG.json
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_CATALOG.md
- docs/media_control_plane_mcp.md
Action:
- Parse route declarations from each listed backend/app/routes/*.py file and route mount statements in backend/app/main.py.
- Parse route entries from API_CATALOG.json and API_CATALOG.md.
- Parse media-control-plane allowed routes from docs/media_control_plane_mcp.md.
- IF same path+method appears in runtime and catalog, mark in_both.
- IF runtime-only and NOT in media-control-plane set, mark runtime_only.
- IF runtime-only and in media-control-plane set, mark control_plane_runtime_only.
- IF catalog-only, mark catalog_only.
- IF same path+method appears in multiple runtime files, mark duplicate.
Expected output:
- Route map matrix with columns: route_key, in_runtime, in_catalog, classification.
PASS condition:
- Every discovered route_key has one of: in_both, runtime_only, control_plane_runtime_only, catalog_only, duplicate.
STOP if:
- Path or method cannot be extracted from any file.

RULE 5
IF route is catalog-only AND route is in media-control-plane docs, THEN action = DO NOT remove route from docs/media_control_plane_mcp.md.
IF route is catalog-only AND route is not in media-control-plane docs, THEN action = mark catalog_only_only.

RULE 6
Input files:
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_USAGE_DIFF.md
- backend/app/routes/*.py
- backend/app/main.py
Action:
- Parse frontend usage lines in API_USAGE_DIFF.md that indicate missing or extra routes.
- IF usage indicates frontend path maps to route that is missing at runtime, mark missing_runtime_route.
- IF runtime route has no frontend usage record, mark unused_runtime_route.
Expected output:
- Usage mismatch list with explicit fields: frontend_path, runtime_presence, catalog_presence, usage_status.
PASS condition:
- Each usage record has an explicit mismatch label or explicit match label.
STOP if:
- Usage record references route that cannot be parsed to method/path.

RULE 7
Input files:
- backend/app/main.py
- backend/app/routes/*.py
- actual_truth_2026-04-24/Aveli_System_Decisions.md
Action:
- IF ambiguous route path maps to multiple runtime routes AND any linked component is marked planned in Aveli_System_Decisions.md, THEN classify as planned_route.
- IF ambiguous route path maps to multiple runtime routes, DO NOT modify any route definition.
- DO NOT merge or delete any ambiguous route definitions.
Expected output:
- Ambiguity table with columns: route_key, matched_routes, planned_linkage, decision.
PASS condition:
- For each ambiguous route, decision is either planned_route or STOP.
STOP if:
- Any ambiguous route has no unambiguous planned linkage.

RULE 8
Input files:
- docs/audit/20260109_aveli_visdom_audit/API_CATALOG.json
- docs/media_control_plane_mcp.md
- backend/app/main.py
- backend/app/routes/*.py
Action:
- IF same route path + method appears in multiple files, mark duplicate_route_conflict.
- IF one duplicate is mounted in backend/app/main.py and others are not, THEN mark unmounted duplicate as legacy_duplicate and DO NOT modify.
- IF all duplicates are mounted, THEN STOP with reason conflict_requires_manual_resolution.
- IF none duplicated routes are mounted, THEN STOP with reason invalid_route_definition.
Expected output:
- Duplicate route classification list.
PASS condition:
- All duplicate cases are assigned one of: legacy_duplicate, conflict_requires_manual_resolution, invalid_route_definition, unknown.
STOP if:
- any duplicate case cannot be resolved by the IF rules.

